<!-- HISTORY -->
<section class="history-section" id="history">
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-num">01</span><div class="gold-line"></div>
    <h2 class="section-title">A <em>History</em> Spanning Centuries</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="history-grid">
    <div class="history-text">
      <p>Chess traces its origins to the ancient Indian game of <em>Chaturanga</em>, played around the 6th century AD, representing the four divisions of the Indian military — infantry, cavalry, elephants, and chariots.</p>
      <p>Traveling westward through Persia (becoming <em>Chatrang</em>, then <em>Shatranj</em>), the game evolved dramatically. When Islamic civilization adopted it, chess flourished across the Arab world, eventually reaching Europe through Spain and Sicily.</p>
      <p>The European Middle Ages transformed pieces to reflect feudal society — the Vizier became the Queen. By the 19th century, chess had standardized, and the first World Championship was held in 1886.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="timeline-item"><span class="timeline-year">~500 AD</span><div class="timeline-event"><strong>Chaturanga — India</strong>The earliest ancestor of chess, played on an 8×8 board called an ashtāpada.</div></div>
      <div class="timeline-item"><span class="timeline-year">600 AD</span><div class="timeline-event"><strong>Shatranj — Persia</strong>"Checkmate" derives from Persian <em>Shāh Māt</em> — "the king is dead."</div></div>
      <div class="timeline-item"><span class="timeline-year">1000 AD</span><div class="timeline-event"><strong>Arrival in Europe</strong>Moorish conquest brings chess to Europe; it spreads across the continent.</div></div>
      <div class="timeline-item"><span class="timeline-year">1475</span><div class="timeline-event"><strong>Modern Rules Emerge</strong>The Queen gains full power. Chess becomes the modern game.</div></div>
      <div class="timeline-item"><span class="timeline-year">1886</span><div class="timeline-event"><strong>First World Championship</strong>Wilhelm Steinitz defeats Zukertort — the first undisputed World Champion.</div></div>
      <div class="timeline-item"><span class="timeline-year">1997</span><div class="timeline-event"><strong>Deep Blue vs. Kasparov</strong>IBM's computer defeats Kasparov — the first time a machine beat a world champion.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

