<!-- RULES -->
<section class="rules-section" id="rules">
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-num">03</span><div class="gold-line"></div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Core <em>Rules</em> <span class="section-hint">— tap to expand</span></h2>
  </div>
  <div class="rules-grid">
    <div class="rule-card" onclick="toggleRule(this)"><div class="rule-number">01</div><div class="rule-title">Check &amp; Checkmate</div><div class="rule-desc">A king in check must escape — checkmate ends the game.</div><div class="rule-extra">When attacked, the player must move the king, block the attack, or capture the attacker. If none is possible, it is checkmate and the game is over.</div></div>
    <div class="rule-card" onclick="toggleRule(this)"><div class="rule-number">02</div><div class="rule-title">Stalemate</div><div class="rule-desc">No legal moves but not in check — an immediate draw.</div><div class="rule-extra">One of chess's most dramatic defensive resources — a losing player can sometimes force stalemate to escape defeat.</div></div>
    <div class="rule-card" onclick="toggleRule(this)"><div class="rule-number">03</div><div class="rule-title">Castling</div><div class="rule-desc">King moves two squares; the rook jumps to the other side.</div><div class="rule-extra">Only legal if: neither piece has moved, no pieces are between them, and the king doesn't pass through check. Both kingside (0-0) and queenside (0-0-0) castling exist.</div></div>
    <div class="rule-card" onclick="toggleRule(this)"><div class="rule-number">04</div><div class="rule-title">En Passant</div><div class="rule-desc">A special pawn capture — available only on the very next move.</div><div class="rule-extra">If a pawn advances two squares and lands beside an opponent's pawn, it may be captured as if it had moved only one. The right expires immediately if not used.</div></div>
    <div class="rule-card" onclick="toggleRule(this)"><div class="rule-number">05</div><div class="rule-title">Promotion</div><div class="rule-desc">A pawn reaching the back rank promotes to any major piece.</div><div class="rule-extra">Promotion is mandatory — almost always to a Queen ("queening"), the most powerful piece. Promoting to a knight is called "underpromotion."</div></div>
    <div class="rule-card" onclick="toggleRule(this)"><div class="rule-number">06</div><div class="rule-title">The 50-Move Rule</div><div class="rule-desc">Draw if no pawn move or capture in 50 moves each.</div><div class="rule-extra">Prevents endless prolonging of unwinnable positions. Either player may claim the draw once the condition is met.</div></div>
  </div>
</section>

