      <p>Algebraic notation is the standard system for recording chess moves. Each square is identified by a file letter (a–h) and rank number (1–8). Piece initials precede the destination square — pawns have no initial.</p>
      <br>
      <p>Special symbols: <em>+</em> check, <em>#</em> checkmate, <em>0-0</em> kingside castling, <em>0-0-0</em> queenside castling, <em>!</em> brilliant move, <em>?</em> mistake.</p>
